1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses the use of Gaussian distributions and maximum-likelihood estimation in the context of machine learning applications, such as signal and image processing and numerical optimization. 
2. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper presents an algorithm for sampling from a Gaussian distribution on the Stiefel manifold and computing the Frechet mean of the samples, which involves numerical computations. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper may be relevant to information theory, as it discusses the statistical analysis of data residing on a Riemannian homogeneous space. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper mentions applications in image processing, which falls under the scope of computer vision and pattern recognition. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper presents an algorithm for computing the Frechet mean of samples drawn from a Gaussian distribution on the Stiefel manifold, which may be of interest to researchers in the field of data structures and algorithms.
